title: Finger Lakes Knickpoints
name: Finger Lakes Knickpoints
description: This layer contains the several knickpoints in the Finger Lakes region of New York state on lakes Cayuga and Seneca.  Knickpoints are a geomorphological indicator that occur on streams where the stream profile changes from normal and concave to steep and convex. Studying the distribution and characteristics of knickpoints and streams can be crucial when trying to explain the evolution of a landscape.
